Couple carrier.Clinical History:

Donor of Mrs. U. Sri Lakshmi (PS) is a comprehensive oocyte donor and has been evaluated for carrier status 
of pathogenic variations.

Single.Clinical History:
Mrs. Seema is of non-consanguineous marriage. Her first pregnancy resulted in missed abortion at 9 
weeks GA. Her second born female child, Miss Aruhi was diagnosed with Joubert syndrome. Whole 
Exome Sequencing in Index, Miss Aruhi (done at Anderson Diagnostics and Labs) was indicative of 
compound heterozygous variants c.1197T>A (likely pathogenic) and c.1414C>T (variant of uncertain 
significance) in AHI1 gene causative of Joubert syndrome 3. Her third pregnancy resulted in missed 
abortion at 13 weeks 4 days GA. Her fourth pregnancy was terminated due to renal/cardiac anomaly. 
Whole Exome sequencing in couple (done at Anderson Diagnostics and Labs) was indicative of father 
and mother to be carriers of likely pathogenic variant c.427C>T in CYP11B1 gene (AR), father carrier for 
likely pathogenic variant c.1197T>A AHI1 gene (AR) and mother carrier for c.1414C>T in AHI1 gene (AR). 
Additionally, father is a carrier for two likely pathogenic variant c.785G>A in GLB1 gene (AR) and 
c.4868delC in ZNF142 gene (AR) and mother is carrier for three likely pathogenic c.1183-1G>A in 
MARVELD2 gene (AR), c.1000C>T in PAPSS2 gene (AR) and c.1327delG in CHRNE gene (AD/AR). Mrs. 
Seema is currently 24 weeks 1 day pregnant. Fetus of Mrs. Seema has been evaluated for pathogenic 
variations.

Single.Clinical History: Mrs. Ashwini is of third-degree consanguineous marriage and her first-born male child was delivered full-term via LSCS and cried immediately after birth. He presented with lethargy, apnea, respiratory alkalosis, and hypoglycemia. His serum ammonia and lactate levels were elevated. New-born Screening test revealed abnormal parameters of organic acid/fatty acids and increased levels of palmitoyl carnitine and low levels of free carnitine. He succumbed at 5 days of life. Carrier Screening by Clinical exome sequencing (done at Anderson Diagnostics & Labs; dated on :06-02-2024; AND23590017617 & AND23590017616) in both the partners revealed they are heterozygous carrier for two likely pathogenic variants SLC25A20: c.496C>T causative of Carnitine acylcarnitine translocase deficiency and C11orf80: c.285dupT causative of Hydatidiform mole, recurrent, 4. Additionally, male partner was found to be heterozygous for two likely pathogenic variants DNAH8: c.12967delA causative of Spermatogenic failure 46 and DNAI1: c.1703G>A causative of Ciliary dyskinesia, primary, 1, with or without situs inversus and one variant of uncertain significance RYR1: c.14707G>A causative of {Malignant hyperthermia susceptibility 1}, Congenital myopathy 1A, autosomal dominant, with susceptibility to malignant hyperthermia, King-Denborough syndrome, Congenital myopathy 1B, autosomal recessive and the female partner is heterozygous for one variant of uncertain significance COL4A4: c.4496A>C causative of Alport syndrome 2, autosomal recessive, Hematuria, familial benign, 1. They have an ongoing pregnancy of ~19 weeks GA (LMP- 21/10/2023). Mrs. Ashwini's brother succumbed to renal failure at 19 years of age. The fetus of Mrs. Ashwini has been evaluated for pathogenic variations.
Single.Disease (omim): Hydatidiform mole, recurrent, 4 (OMIM#618432)

She is presented with chief complaints of cold feet, prinking feeling in feet, numbness in hand and leg fingers, cold weather intolerance, muscle weakness and sleep disturbances since 40 years of age. Proband's mother had similar complaints and second elder brother has muscle stiffness and weakness. The Charcot-Marie-Tooth 1A/HNPP [PMP22, COX10, TEKT3] deletion/duplication analysis done at Anderson Diagnostics [PIN: AND23150029981; Date: 03.04.2024] revealed no pathogenic or likely pathogenic deletions / duplications in PMP22, COX10 and TEKT3 genes.
